This paper presents a density-based clustering algorithm that can handle arbitrary data and distance functions, making it relevant to the database (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The algorithm's scalability and incremental nature also make it relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) community. Finally, the paper mentions the use of the algorithm for information retrieval (cs.IR), indicating its potential relevance to that community as well.
